  "body": "Many users are using `out_file` to dump buffer contents with `<secondary>` section when buffered output plugins are failing flush.\nBut `out_file` is too complex and with too many features for such purpose. We cannot assure anything if users use complex configuration in `<secondary>` section.\n\nI propose a new plugin only for `<secondary>` section just to dump buffer contents to a path on local host, with just few, minimum # of options/parameters.\n\nTo be considered:\n- Is it enough to support local disk only? any others?\n- Can we re-format these records in any specific format to make it possible to extract/read dumped files by a utility command?\n",
